 DESPITE Villarreal manager, Unai Emery insistence that Samuel Chukwueze is not for sale more clubs have started making enquiries about the Nigerian with a view to luring him away from the Yellow Submarines. Liverpool, Real Madrid and Everton have reportedly indicated interest in the Super Eagles left footer but Manchester United and also joined the fray as reported by La Razon. The medium pointed out that the Red Devils are eager to tempt Chukwueze away from Spain with the aim of helping him achieve his dream of playing in the English Premier League.  It was also gathered that the 21-year-old has also impressed Chelsea other sources indicated that the Blues were yet to put in an official bid. The Nigerian who is still under contract with Villarreal until June 30, 2023 has played nine La Liga Santander matches with a goal and assists to his credit.